## How to use this file

This is Claude Code's persistent global context — loaded into every conversation. List repos / projects you actively touch and a one-line description, so Claude can navigate without re-asking each session.

Convention: top-level `## <repo-name>` heading per project, with `Path:`, brief description, entry doc (`@/path/to/README.md`), and a "read on demand" list of key files. Keep entries to ~10 lines each; Claude can always read the actual file when it needs depth.

---

## (Sample — replace with your own projects)

### my-flagship-repo

Path: `~/my-flagship-repo`
One-line description of what this repo does and why it matters.

Entry doc:
@~/my-flagship-repo/README.md

Other key files (read on demand):
- `src/` — source layout
- `tests/` — pytest / vitest / etc.
- `docs/architecture.md` — high-level system diagram

---

## Tips

- Use absolute paths (`~/foo` works on POSIX; on Windows write `C:\Users\{{ .chezmoi.username }}\foo` or rely on `$env:USERPROFILE\foo`).
- `@/path/to/file.md` syntax tells Claude to *eagerly* include that file; reserve it for entry docs you want loaded every session.
- Save personal preferences (tone, language, never-do rules) under `~/.claude/projects/<dir>/memory/` so they persist across sessions without bloating this file.
